## Dependency updates (2026-07-18)
- [x] composer update --with-all-dependencies within existing constraints —
      composer audit now reports zero advisories (was 21). Also required
      installing composer itself into insights-app (wasn't there at all);
      persisted via docker/setup-dev-container.sh for future rebuilds.
- [x] npm update for vite, axios, autoprefixer, concurrently, lightningcss —
      npm audit reports zero vulnerabilities.
- [x] tailwindcss/@tailwindcss/vite/@tailwindcss/oxide initially pinned to
      exact 4.1.17 (npm update had pulled 4.3.3, whose oxide native binding
      requires Node >= 20, but insights-vite ran Node 18). Resolved properly
      by bumping insights-vite's docker-compose image to node:20 and
      unpinning back to the original ^4.0.7 caret range — now on 4.3.3
      cleanly, no EBADENGINE warnings. Verified dev server + build + browser
      render.
- [ ] laravel/pint bumped 1.27.1 -> 1.29.3 as part of this update and now
      flags ~19 pre-existing files (tests/, routes/, factories/, seeders/)
      for new default style rules (fully_qualified_strict_types,
      ordered_imports, no_unused_imports) that weren't enforced before.
      Not touched — a repo-wide Pint reformat is a separate, deliberate
      commit, not a side effect of a dependency bump.
- [x] Laravel 13 / Pest 4 / Laravel Boost 2.x — researched breaking changes
      first (see memory), then upgraded. Had to also bump
      barryvdh/laravel-debugbar ^3.15.2 -> ^4.0 (3.x doesn't support
      Laravel 13) and update bootstrap/providers.php since debugbar 4.x
      renamed its service provider namespace (Barryvdh\Debugbar ->
      Fruitcake\LaravelDebugbar, no back-compat alias). Full Pest suite
      (43 tests) passes, PHPStan unchanged (237 pre-existing notices),
      verified live in browser.

