## Categorization UX pass (2026-07-18)
- [x] Optimistic category save — pill shows instantly (pulsing) on click via a
      client-side categoryLookup, $wire.saveCategory() called directly (not
      through a dispatch/listener round trip) so it returns a promise to
      reconcile/rollback on. Replaces the old modal Save button entirely —
      picking a category now saves immediately.
- [x] Replaced the flat category <select> in the assign-category modal with a
      searchable/filterable list (client-side filter over categoryList, no
      server round trip per keystroke)
- [x] Merchant-based category suggestions — computed per-page in with() via
      merchantSuggestions(), surfaced as an inline "+ Category?" quick-apply
      chip next to uncategorized transactions, and pinned at the top of the
      modal when opened via "+". Groundwork for future auto-categorization.
- [x] Explicitly deprioritized: favorites / most-used quick-pick chips
- [x] Create category from the assign-category popup (2026-07-18) — a
      "+ Create new category" option swaps the modal's content to a
      name/parent/color form; submitting creates it, merges it into the
      client-side category list, and applies it via the same optimistic
      flow as picking an existing category. Regression tests added.
- [x] Touch-friendly category delete (2026-07-18) — replaced the
      mouseover/mouseout Alpine toggle with pure CSS (always 70%
      opacity, full opacity on :hover), no device detection needed.
      Verified visible + tappable on a fresh page load with zero mouse
      interaction.
- [x] Mobile spot-check (2026-07-18) of the two features above at a
      390px viewport: assign-category modal (including the "+ Create
      new category" button pinned below the scrollable list) and the
      new Create Category form (name/parent/color) both fit within
      the viewport with no page-level overflow, only the intended
      internal list scroll. Full create-and-assign flow (type name ->
      Create & Assign) verified end-to-end, and the always-visible
      delete "x" on the category pill confirmed visible/tappable with
      zero hover. No new issues found.

