## Later / exploratory (raised by Andres, not scheduled)
- [ ] Look into Livewire @islands to scope re-renders to just the changed
      row + chart instead of the whole transactions component
- [ ] Found while adding createCategory() tests: Category::fullName() and
      Category::descendants() cache by id in a *static* class-level array
      with no invalidation. Harmless per-request in normal (non-Octane)
      usage, but stale across anything that reuses ids without a fresh
      PHP process — including this project's own Pest runs under
      RefreshDatabase, where one test's cached name/descendants for an id
      can leak into a later test that reuses that same id. Worth deciding
      whether to remove the cache, key it differently, or add an
      invalidation path (e.g. clear on save/rename).
